us million q  net income us million q  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  number of employees  website wwwsandridgeenergycom sandridge energy inc is a petroleum and natural gas exploration company headquartered in oklahoma city united states contents  history  operations  references  external links historyedit sandridge was founded in  by tom l ward by buying approximately  of riata energy of amarillo texas ward previously cofounded chesapeake energy with aubrey mcclendon and was the chief operating officer of that company from  until  the company went public via an initial public offering on november   selling over  million common shares on june   after a series of missteps ceo tom l ward was ousted by the board of the directors and james bennett became president and ceo bennett first joined the company in  and previously worked at gso capital partners in  the company sold its assets in the gulf of mexico for  million in  the company acquired pinon gathering company owner of  miles of gathering lines which reduced sandridges lease operating and gathering expense it also acquired  net acres in the niobara shale formation for  million in cash by then the local fracking boom had largely played out and the economies of harper sumner and adjacent southern kansas and northern oklahoma counties suffered under the impact earthquakes due to induced seismicity produced by injected wastes had also substantially reduced in frequency and intensity thanks to a kansas corporation commission order mandating cutbacks in injection well volumes and pressures sandridge which along with chesapeake energy was one of the two major producers in southcentral kansas appealed the order but soon went into bankruptcy in  the company went through a chapter  bankruptcy reorganization operationsedit in the third quarter of  the company produced  thousand barrels of oil equivalent  gj per day sandridge owns oil properties in the midcontinent which accounts for  of production it also owns properties in the permian basin west texas and in the niobrara formation of colorado the company has formed  public royalty trusts sandridge permian trust nyse per  owner of royalty interests in oil and natural gas properties in the central basin platform of the permian basin in andrews county texas sandridge mississippian trust i nyse sdt  owner of royalty interests in oil and natural gas properties in the mississippian formation in alfalfa garfield grant and woods counties in oklahoma sandridge mississippian trust ii nyse sdr  owner of royalty interests in oil and natural gas properties in the mississippian formation in alfalfa grant kay noble and woods counties in northern oklahoma and barber comanche harper and sumner counties in southern kansas referencesedit  a b c d e f g sandridge energy inc form q quarterly report  richard finger february   tom ward of sandridge energy another ceo thats got to go forbes magazine   sandridge energy inc prices initial public offering press release prnewswire november     sandridge energy board ousts founder tom ward cnbc june     sandridge management team  sandridge to sell gulf of mexico business for  million bloomberg lp january     sandridge energy inc announces acquisition of pinon gathering company llc press release prnewswire october     sandridge energy inc acquires north park basin niobrara shale oil assets for  million in cash prnewswire november     downward flows ripples oil gas downturn hitting counties on many levels kansas agland amy bickel feb   retrieved  march   fracking divides small town of anthony kansas university daily kansan rebecca dowd jul   retrieved  march   increasing number of earthquakes prompts new regulations in kansas oklahoma oil industries kmuw abigail beckman january   retrieved  march   adam wilmoth october   sandridge energy emerges from bankruptcy newsok  external linksedit official sandridge energy website v t e major corporations within the oklahoma city metropolitan area nyse li